The paper deals with the problem of dictionary learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and signal processing. The paper proposes a novel framework for dictionary update, which involves optimizing an over-complete dictionary with a given sparsity pattern. This problem is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), information theory (cs.IT), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and signal processing (cs.SI). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with learning and processing signals.
